description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for an occupational therapist to join our team of physios and OTs in the Mainstream Schools Team, based at Ryegate Children&#39;s Centre and part of Sheffield Children&#39;s NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part-time post (24.4 hours/week), based at Ryegate (and currently some home working due to Covid 19) with additional travel within Sheffield to visit children in their home and school settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has a passion for working with children with disabilties to join a friendly, experienced and dynamic team. You will need good basic OT skills and experience, enthusiasm, flexibility, excellent communication skills and great team work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like you, we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
